# Rav Legacy RAG API ‚Äî Project Overview

## What this system is

A production-grade RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) API that answers questions about
Rav Soloveitchik's recorded teachings. Transcripts (`.srt` / `.txt`) are chunked, embedded
into a vector store, and retrieved at query time to ground LLM responses with cited sources.

**Full spec**: `specs/current/architecture.md`

## Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| API framework | FastAPI 1.0.0 (`rag.app.main`) |
| Webhook API | FastAPI ‚Äî separate process (`rag.app.webhook`), CMS sync receiver |
| Embeddings | Google Gemini (`gemini-embedding-001`) |
| LLM | Gemini Flash / GPT-5.2 (switchable via `LLM_CONFIGURATION`) |
| Vector store | Pinecone **or** MongoDB Atlas Vector (switchable via `DATABASE_CONFIGURATION`) |
| Auth | Supabase JWT (`app/services/auth.py`) |
| Rate limiting | Upstash Redis (optional ‚Äî disabled when token absent) |
| Query persistence | Supabase RPC `submit_user_query` |
| Metrics / exceptions logging | MongoDB |

## Module map

| Directory | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| `app/api/v1/` | HTTP routers ‚Äî no business logic |
| `app/services/` | Business logic (embedding, LLM, auth, sync) |
| `app/db/` | Database connections and retrieval |
| `app/schemas/` | Pydantic contracts (requests, responses, enums) |
| `app/models/` | Internal domain models (not exposed directly) |
| `app/core/config.py` | `Settings` / `SharedSettings` ‚Äî Pydantic settings |
| `app/core/webhook_config.py` | `WebhookSettings` ‚Äî extends `SharedSettings`; no auth/Redis/Supabase required |
| `app/core/constants/` | Non-secret defaults (env-overridable) |
| `app/webhook.py` | Webhook API entrypoint ‚Äî separate FastAPI process for CMS sync |
| `app/exceptions/` | Typed exception hierarchy |
| `scripts/` | Ingestion and sync scripts |
| `smoke_tests/` | End-to-end smoke test runner + spec |
| `specs/current/` | Canonical system state ‚Äî architecture, API, data models, config |
| `specs/features/` | Feature specs (`what.md`, `how.md`, `test.md`, `changes.yaml`) |
| `specs/bugs/` | Bug specs (same structure as features) |
| `specs/index.yaml` | Registry of all features and bugs |
| `specs/tools/spec` | CLI to scaffold new specs (`spec create feature <slug>`) |
| `.cursor/skills/` | Cursor agent skills (registered, slash-command accessible) |

## Critical invariants

- **Secrets only in `.env`** ‚Äî never in `app/core/constants/` or committed to source control.
- **Constants are defaults, not config** ‚Äî every constant must be overridable via its `Settings` field.
- **No business logic in routers** ‚Äî routers validate input and delegate to `app/services/`.
- **Typed exceptions only** ‚Äî raise from `app/exceptions/`, never bare `Exception` or `HTTPException` directly in services.
- Start the RAG API: `PYTHONPATH=.. uvicorn rag.app.main:app --port 8000`
- Start the Webhook API (separate process): `PYTHONPATH=.. uvicorn rag.app.webhook:app --port 8001`
- **Webhook endpoints are not JWT-protected** ‚Äî secured via HMAC (`webhook_secret`). Never add `verify_jwt_token` to webhook handlers.
